The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 ID cards for Bengal

 New Delhi, May 25: The multi-purpose national identity cards will be delivered in 20 centres, including Bengals Murshidabad, from tomorrow.

 About 2 lakh people will get the cards within two months. Karimganj in Assam and West Tripura are among the centres that are part of the trial run.

 The card carries a 16-kilobyte microprocessor chip with a unique 16-digit identification number.

 It is expected to make citizens interface with the government more user-friendly and act as a deterrent to illegal immigration.




